From 1c73bd8e65361e95438d06a357ded854624109be Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yi Ding <yi.s.ding@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 15:13:13 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 8/9] fix rkmpp code review issues

- rkmppdec: make rkmpp_export_frame always consume the MppFrame so
  error paths no longer double-free it or leak the DRM descriptor and
  tmp_frame
- rkmppdec: fix assignment binding on info_change so it only stores
  MPP's real info-change flag
- rkmppdec: honor AV_EF_EXPLODE for hardware-flagged errinfo frames
- rkmppenc: fully unwind the MPPEncFrame entry when submit fails so a
  bufferless frame is never queued for encoding or leaked
- rkmppenc: reclaim the consumed input frame's buffer on
  rkmpp_get_packet error exits; check av_frame_clone result
- rkrga: don't free frames already consumed by ff_filter_frame; check
  av_frame_clone result in submit_frame
- hwcontext_rkmpp: compute pool buffer size in size_t to avoid signed
  overflow on large frames
- pixdesc: rename NV20_PACKED descriptor to nv20_packed to stop
  hijacking av_get_pix_fmt("nv20") from AV_PIX_FMT_NV20LE/BE
- lavc/Makefile: add SKIPHEADERS for rkmpp headers to unbreak
  checkheaders without MPP installed

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
